arnassensis 2.22 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]: <i>neuter</i> <i>plural</i> κράτιστα as <i>adverb</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “HG” 3.4.16, “Ages.” 1.25.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —The _comparative_ in use is κρείσσων (which see).","strongNumber":"G2903","accentedUnicode":"κράτιστος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2904","matchingForm":"κράτος","stepTransliteration":"kratos","gloss":"power","_zh_tw_Gloss":"權能","_es_Gloss":"poder","_zh_Gloss":"权能"}],"shortDef":"most excellent, \"your Excellency\"","mediumDef":"most excellent, \"your Excellency\" <br /><b>strongest;</b>, in NT <greek>κράτιστε</greek>, a term of respect, <b>most excellent, noble,</b> or <b>illustrious,</b> <ref='Luk.1.3'>Lk. 1:3</ref>; <ref='Act.23.26'>Acts 23:26;</ref> 24:3; 26:25*","stepGloss":"excellent","stepTransliteration":"kratistos","count":4,"_es_Definition":"excelentísimo, su excelencia (uso de etiqueta cortés y al dirigirse a la nobleza)","_zh_tw_Definition":"閣下; 大人 (敬辭, 用於尊稱身份高貴的人)","_zh_Definition":"阁下; 大人 (敬辞, 用于尊称身份高贵的人)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"rất kính mến; đáng kính","_zh_tw_Gloss":"大人","_es_Gloss":"excelente","_zh_Gloss":"大人"}]}